# Date Exploration Findings

## Date Coverage

- First Order Date: 2010-12-29
- Last Order Date: 2014-01-28
- Historical Coverage: 37 months

### Insight
The dataset contains over three years of transactional history, providing sufficient data for trend and seasonality analysis.

---

## Orders by Year

| Year | Orders |
|------|--------:|
| 2010 | 14 |
| 2011 | 2,216 |
| 2012 | 3,269 |
| 2013 | 21,287 |
| 2014 | 871 |

### Insight
Order volume increased significantly over time. The 2014 data appears incomplete and should be treated cautiously in trend analysis.

---

## Sales by Year

| Year | Sales |
|------|-------:|
| 2010 | 43,419 |
| 2011 | 7,075,088 |
| 2012 | 5,842,231 |
| 2013 | 16,344,878 |
| 2014 | 45,642 |

### Insight
Sales peaked in 2013 with substantial growth compared to previous years.

---

### Average Order Value

| Year | Average Order Value |
|------|---------------------:|
| 2010 | 3101.36 |
| 2011 | 3192.73 |
| 2012 | 1787.16 |
| 2013 | 767.83 |
| 2014 | 52.40 |

#### Insight
Despite increasing order volume over time, average order value shows a strong downward trend, indicating a shift toward lower-value transactions or changes in product mix.

---

## Quarterly Sales (2013 Focus)

| Quarter | Sales |
|---------|--------:|
| Q1 | 2,678,708 |
| Q2 | 3,973,264 |
| Q3 | 4,364,829 |
| Q4 | 5,328,077 |

### Insight
2013 shows a consistent quarter-over-quarter growth pattern, indicating strong and sustained business expansion throughout the year. Q4 represents the peak performance period.